Start a code rules document: doc/claude/CODE.md
- Function names should indicate what a function does. Keep them short but prevent ambiguity.
- A function should do one thing, split it up when different algorithms are there.
- Try to prevent code duplication by creating helper functions.
- Variable-, argument-, and field names should indicate what data it holds. Keep them short but prevent ambiguity.
- Documentation above a function should not describe what is does but why it should be used.
- Only when an algorithm is unclear write documentation inside a function.
- When the same fields are given as an argument on many functions, try to move them to a common struct.

Are these rules clear, can you describe what conclusions they lead to.

